      "amount": "2-3 slices (adjust based on spice preference)"
    },
    {
      "name": "Garlic Cloves",
      "amount": "3 cloves, minced"
    },
    {
      "name": "Water or Chicken Broth",
      "amount": "1/4 cup"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a pan over medium heat.",
    "Add almonds and sesame seeds to the pan. Stir-fry for about 2 minutes until lightly toasted.",
    "Add minced ginger, garlic, and chili peppers (or sliced red pepper flakes). Sauté for another minute.",
    "Pour water or broth into the pan and stir well to combine.",
    "Stir in red pepper flakes and let it simmer for a few seconds more.",
    "Reduce heat to low, cover the pan, and cook until liquid is absorbed and almonds are crispy (about 5 minutes).",
    "Remove from heat and serve hot."
  ],
